      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "With a manual transmission, it must go full-throttle during the test. However, automatic transmissions don’t go through the same procedure. That’s the kicker is a different transmission can cause a car which would flunk the state’s test to pass. In other words, a rule which ostensibly is supposed to combat noise pollution in the Golden State is actually quite arbitrary, at least in certain ways.",
